INSERT INTO agent_reference_docs (
  id, offering_id, category_id, lens, doc_type, audience, title, content_md,
  extends_doc_id, status, version
) VALUES (
  '66af9422-5a07-4ed5-b089-8d3824403e01',
  '6c8f72f0-887f-484a-a588-0bb9bd8052c9',
  '138ed383-364a-44a3-87a0-8e641ecd4200',
  'clinical', 'clinical_summary', 'provider',
  'Juvederm Voluma XC — Clinical Summary',
  E'## Product Identity\n\nJuvederm Voluma XC is a cross-linked hyaluronic acid dermal filler manufactured by Allergan Aesthetics (AbbVie). It uses **Vycross technology** — a blend of high- and low-molecular-weight HA chains that produces a highly cohesive, firmer gel than conventional BDDE cross-linked HA. HA concentration: 20 mg/mL. Contains 0.3% lidocaine. [FDA label Juvederm Voluma XC NDA 125474]\n\n## Mechanism of Action\n\nVycross cross-linking creates a high-G'' (elastic modulus) gel estimated at approximately 800 Pa — among the highest lift capacity in the Juvederm portfolio. This high G'' enables structural support in volumetric planes where a softer gel would compress without lift. HA is inherently biocompatible and biodegradable; cross-linking slows enzymatic degradation, extending duration. [peer-reviewed: Sundaram H. J Drugs Dermatol 2015]\n\nClinical effect: injectable volumizer providing structural lift and projection in the midface and chin. Not a surface or line filler — product is optimized for deep plane injection. [FDA label]\n\n## FDA-Cleared Indications\n\n- **Cheek augmentation** to correct age-related volume loss in adults aged ≥21 (FDA approval 2013) [FDA label]\n- **Chin region augmentation** for adults aged ≥22, with or without chin projection (FDA approval 2021) [FDA label]\n\n**Gateway posture — off-label:** Voluma is commonly used off-label for temple augmentation, jawline enhancement, and nasal dorsum augmentation. These are field-standard practices not endorsed by FDA labeling. [field practice] Sources differ on optimal depth and volume for off-label sites; see relevant technique literature for detail.\n\n## Candidacy\n\n**Ideal candidate profile:** Adults with midface volume loss creating a flattened or descended cheek appearance. Patients with adequate skin elasticity who will show lift with volumetric correction. Chin candidacy: patients seeking chin projection or definition without surgical implant. [FDA label; peer-reviewed: Jones D. Aesthet Surg J 2016]\n\n**Poor candidacy signals:**\n- Active or recent infection, inflammation, or skin disease at injection site\n- History of anaphylaxis or severe allergy to HA products or gram-positive bacterial proteins\n- Known bleeding disorder or anticoagulation therapy increasing bruise/hematoma risk\n- Patients with unrealistic expectations (structural volume correction, not skin quality)\n- Very thin facial fat compartments where deep injection would be superficial in practice [FDA label]\n\n## Safety Profile\n\n**Adverse events (FDA label — authority rank 1):**\n- Common (>5%): injection site tenderness, swelling, firmness, lumps/bumps, bruising, discoloration, pain. Typically resolve within 2-4 weeks. [FDA label]\n- Uncommon: prolonged edema, asymmetry, inflammatory nodule formation\n- Rare but serious: **vascular occlusion** — product is high-G'' and injected in deep planes; intra-arterial injection risk exists, particularly at the nasal dorsum, glabella, and temporal vessels. Must be familiar with facial vascular anatomy and reversal with hyaluronidase before injecting. [FDA label; peer-reviewed: DeLorenzi C. Aesthet Surg J 2014]\n- Late inflammatory nodule (LIN): rare delayed hypersensitivity, may appear weeks to years post-injection; managed with hyaluronidase, intralesional steroids, or both [peer-reviewed: Cassuto D. J Cosmet Dermatol 2021]\n\n**Contraindications:** Hypersensitivity to HA or lidocaine; active infection at injection site. [FDA label]\n\n**Reversal:** Hyaluronidase (Vitrase, Hylenex) is effective for dissolution. Emergency protocol should be established before each treatment session. [field practice consensus]\n\n## Clinical Outcomes Data\n\nPivotal trial (FDA submission): cheek augmentation. Responder rate (≥1-point MFVAS improvement at 6 months): ~82%. Duration data: 24 months in pivotal studies; real-world duration commonly cited as 12-24 months depending on area, volume injected, and patient metabolism. [FDA label; peer-reviewed: Baumann L. Aesthet Surg J 2015]\n\nGateway posture: "Duration is 12-24 months depending on individual factors — for exact protocol and retreatment intervals, see the Juvederm Voluma XC prescribing information [FDA/DailyMed →]."',
  '02f611ad-cd03-464c-ab1a-a06bd4ead0cf',
  'draft', 1
);

INSERT INTO agent_reference_docs (
  id, offering_id, category_id, lens, doc_type, audience, title, content_md,
  extends_doc_id, status, version
) VALUES (
  '68e7f52a-c9d5-406d-92a2-94093784c836',
  '6c8f72f0-887f-484a-a588-0bb9bd8052c9',
  '138ed383-364a-44a3-87a0-8e641ecd4200',
  'clinical', 'technique_guide', 'provider',
  'Juvederm Voluma XC — Technique Guide',
  E'## Injection Planes\n\nVoluma XC is a deep tissue product. The appropriate injection planes by indication:\n\n- **Cheek augmentation:** Deep subdermal to supraperiosteal plane. The medial cheek fat compartment (SOOF level) and zygomatic arch periosteal depot are the primary targets for volumetric lift. Avoid superficial intradermal placement — Voluma''s high G'' creates visible/palpable ridging if too shallow. [FDA label; peer-reviewed: Rohrich R. Plast Reconstr Surg 2019]\n\n- **Chin augmentation:** Supraperiosteal plane on the chin eminence and labiomental fold. Product placed at bone level to create structural projection. Midline and paramedian placement depending on chin morphology. [FDA label; consensus]\n\n**Gateway posture for injection depth:** Exact technique (cannula vs needle, angle, depth to periosteum) varies with anatomy; sources differ on optimal approach. For exact protocol, see the Juvederm Voluma XC prescribing information and the FDA-approved technique documentation [FDA/DailyMed →].\n\n## Dosing Zones (Range Characterization)\n\nTotal volumes reported in clinical trials and field practice — presented as ranges, not a prescriptive protocol:\n\n- Cheeks (bilateral): approximately 2-6 mL total across both sides depending on degree of volume deficit\n- Chin: approximately 0.5-2 mL depending on projection goal and baseline anatomy\n- Per-session volumes commonly cited: 4 mL or less for initial treatment; touchup at 4-6 weeks [FDA label; field practice]\n\n**Gateway pointer:** For exact per-area dosing recommendations, refer to the Voluma XC Prescribing Information and Clinical Reference Guide from Allergan Aesthetics [FDA/DailyMed →].\n\n## Technique Notes\n\n- **Product cohesivity:** Vycross product is cohesive and may require firm pressure to express. Needle gauge 27G; cannula 25G typical. [field practice]\n- **Bolus vs. fanning:** Deep volumetric areas typically use bolus depot technique; layering with threads in more superficial refinement passes is described [peer-reviewed: Vleggaar D. J Drugs Dermatol 2016]\n- **Massage:** Post-injection massage used to distribute product smoothly; gentle shaping to avoid clumping. More aggressive with high-G'' products in deep planes.\n- **Tenting:** Pinch test to confirm pre-injection depth; tenting through skin indicates product is too superficial for this indication. [FDA label]\n\n## Treatment Planning\n\n- Pre-treat with topical EMLA or ice; lidocaine in product provides additional comfort during injection\n- Mark injection sites pre-treatment to guide symmetrical placement\n- Combination planning: Voluma for structural lift → layered with softer products (e.g., Vollure XC, Ultra XC) for fine line and perioral correction as a separate or same-session treatment (approved pairings per item_relationships)\n- Retreatment interval: clinical data supports 24-month duration; individual retreatment schedule varies [FDA label]\n\n## Combination Sequencing\n\nWithin the Juvederm portfolio, Voluma is typically the structural foundation product. Sequence from deep to superficial and large bolus to fine line correction. Filler sequencing rationale: correct anatomical support/lift plane first; then address surface irregularities [field practice consensus]. Sources differ on same-session vs. staged approach; gateway posture applies.',
  '202c5649-f39a-4cfb-a894-5913ad490b47',
  'draft', 1
);

INSERT INTO agent_reference_docs (
  id, offering_id, category_id, lens, doc_type, audience, title, content_md,
  extends_doc_id, status, version
) VALUES (
  '823e604a-b52b-46eb-ba17-b5f61ddb238a',
  '6c8f72f0-887f-484a-a588-0bb9bd8052c9',
  '138ed383-364a-44a3-87a0-8e641ecd4200',
  'sales_education', 'patient_education', 'patient',
  'Juvederm Voluma XC — Patient Education',
  E'## What It Does for You\n\nJuvederm Voluma XC is the original FDA-approved cheek filler — the product specifically designed to restore the volume your face naturally had when you were younger. Over time, the fat pads in your face migrate downward and the underlying bone subtly resorbs, leaving cheeks looking flat, hollow, or aged. Voluma works deep beneath the skin to rebuild that structural foundation and restore cheek fullness from within.\n\nThe result isn''t "filled" — it''s lifted. When volume is placed at the right anatomical level, the whole midface elevates, nasolabial folds soften, and the face reads younger without looking done. This is why Voluma is often called the "liquid facelift" product: it addresses the root cause of midface aging rather than chasing individual lines.\n\nVoluma XC is also FDA-approved to augment the chin — adding projection and definition to a chin that recedes or lacks balance with the rest of the face.\n\n## Why Voluma, Specifically\n\nNot all fillers are the same product with different labels. Voluma uses Vycross technology — a unique cross-linking approach that creates a firmer, more cohesive gel purpose-built for structural lift. Softer fillers collapse under gravitational load in deep planes; Voluma holds shape because it was designed to. This is the right tool for volumetric correction.\n\nThe lidocaine in the formula means the injection itself is far more comfortable than older filler formulations.\n\n## What to Expect\n\n**During the session:** Your injector will cleanse and mark the treatment areas, then inject Voluma using a fine needle. The session typically takes 30-60 minutes depending on how many areas are treated. The lidocaine in the product provides comfort during injection.\n\n**Right after:** You will see immediate improvement in cheek volume, though some swelling and bruising is expected. The final result settles in fully over 2-4 weeks as initial swelling resolves.\n\n**How long it lasts:** Clinical studies show Voluma results lasting up to 24 months — longer than most other HA fillers, making it one of the most cost-effective per-month filler options available.\n\n## Benefit Framing\n\nThe value proposition of Voluma is restoration of structural architecture — not surface treatment. Patients who have tried lighter fillers and been disappointed often find that their concern was never about lines or texture — it was about the midface architecture. Voluma corrects the architecture.\n\n**A note on cost:** Voluma is typically priced per syringe with most patients needing 2-4 syringes at an initial session. Spread over a 2-year lifespan, the monthly cost is comparable to a skincare subscription — but the result is visible every day without applying anything.\n\n## Combination Therapy\n\nVoluma is the structural foundation in a comprehensive facial rejuvenation plan. Most patients benefit from a layered approach:\n- Voluma XC for midface volume and lift (structural layer)\n- A softer Juvederm product (Vollure XC or Ultra XC) for perioral lines and nasolabial softening\n- Neurotoxin (Botox, Dysport) for dynamic lines that a filler cannot address\n\nThis combination produces a complete result — architecture, surface, and movement all addressed. Your injector will recommend which additional treatments, if any, will complete your specific result.\n\n## Maintenance\n\nVoluma lasts 18-24 months in most patients, and results can be maintained by returning for a touchup treatment before full resorption. Many patients find that maintaining volume over time requires less product per session than the initial correction — this is because the tissue infrastructure is being supported rather than rebuilt from baseline.',
  'e2e32141-cf83-4475-a94d-1aafafe8d66e',
  'draft', 1
);

INSERT INTO agent_reference_docs (
  id, offering_id, category_id, lens, doc_type, audience, title, content_md,
  extends_doc_id, status, version
) VALUES (
  '8530bea8-f59c-4805-867e-5cd42437dd75',
  '6c8f72f0-887f-484a-a588-0bb9bd8052c9',
  '138ed383-364a-44a3-87a0-8e641ecd4200',
  'sales_education', 'faq', 'patient',
  'Juvederm Voluma XC — FAQ',
  E'## Common Questions\n\n**"Will it look natural?"**\nWhen placed correctly by a skilled injector, Voluma is designed to look like you — just refreshed. The goal is structural restoration, not transformation. The best results feel like people noticing you look well-rested without knowing why.\n\n**"I''m nervous about looking overdone."**\nThis is the most common concern before a first filler treatment. Voluma placed at the correct volume for your anatomy lifts and restores — it doesn''t puff or inflate. You are always in control of how much is placed, and the Vycross technology creates a natural-feeling result rather than a stiff or artificial one. The lidocaine also means you''re comfortable throughout.\n\n**"What if I don''t like it?"**\nHA fillers including Voluma can be dissolved with hyaluronidase enzyme — this is one of the key safety advantages of HA-based products. Reversal is not instant, but it is effective. Discuss this with your injector before treatment.\n\n**"Is it worth the cost?"**\nVoluma''s 24-month duration is one of the longest among HA fillers, which affects the value calculation significantly. When you divide the cost by months of result, Voluma is often the most cost-effective structural filler option. Many patients also find they need less product at maintenance sessions than at their initial correction.\n\n**"Does it hurt?"**\nThe formula contains 0.3% lidocaine, which provides significant comfort improvement over unblended filler. The deep plane of injection means you''re not working in the more sensitive surface layers. Most patients describe the experience as tolerable to comfortable.\n\n**"How is this different from Botox?"**\nBotox relaxes muscles to soften movement-related lines. Voluma is a structural volumizer — it does not affect muscle movement. They work on completely different mechanisms and address completely different concerns. Many patients benefit from both for a complete result.\n\n## Objection Reframes\n\n**"I''m not ready to look different."**\nVoluma is about looking like yourself again — not different. Volume loss is what makes the face read as aged; restoring it is restoration, not change. The goal is for people to say you look great, not "what did you do?"\n\n**"I''ll wait until it''s worse."**\nEarlier intervention requires less product and produces more natural results because the underlying structure still has support. Waiting until volume loss is significant often means more product is needed and the foundation requires more rebuilding. Maintenance is easier than correction from a severe baseline.\n\n**"I read about filler complications online."**\nSerious complications are real but rare, and occur primarily with improperly placed or very large volumes in high-risk anatomical zones. Choosing a trained, experienced injector significantly reduces this risk. Your injector can explain their safety protocols, including emergency reversal preparation.',
  'e2e32141-cf83-4475-a94d-1aafafe8d66e',
  'draft', 1
);

INSERT INTO agent_reference_docs (
  id, offering_id, category_id, lens, doc_type, audience, title, content_md,
  extends_doc_id, status, version
) VALUES (
  '8686de86-154c-4883-8350-24d02c04cd59',
  '6c8f72f0-887f-484a-a588-0bb9bd8052c9',
  '138ed383-364a-44a3-87a0-8e641ecd4200',
  'deep_product', 'deep_dive_playbook', 'provider',
  'Juvederm Voluma XC — Deep Dive Playbook',
  E'## Differentiation\n\nVoluma XC holds a unique position in the HA filler landscape as the only HA product with FDA cheek augmentation AND FDA chin augmentation indications. Within the Allergan portfolio, it is the highest G'' filler — the structural anchor. This differentiation matters clinically: choosing Voluma when Vollure or Ultra XC would serve the same indication overfills volume planes; choosing a softer product when Voluma''s lift capacity is needed under-corrects.\n\nVersus Restylane Lyft: Both products have FDA cheek and hand volume indications. Voluma uses Vycross cross-linking (higher cohesivity, long duration); Lyft uses OBT (Optimal Balance Technology — modified NASHA gel). Duration profiles are comparable; technique preferences vary by injector and patient anatomy.\n\n## Mechanism Detail\n\n**Vycross technology:**\nConventional HA fillers use BDDE cross-linking of high-molecular-weight (HMW) HA only. Vycross blends a small proportion of low-molecular-weight (LMW) HA with HMW HA before BDDE cross-linking. The LMW HA participates as a "chain spacer" — the resulting network has more cross-links per unit volume with less free HA. This produces:\n- Higher G'' (elastic modulus): ~800 Pa for Voluma vs ~300 Pa for Juvederm Ultra\n- Lower swelling ratio (less hygroscopic expansion post-injection)\n- Longer duration (slower enzymatic degradation of the denser network)\n[peer-reviewed: Sundaram H. J Drugs Dermatol 2015]\n\n## Evidence Summary\n\n**Pivotal study (cheek):** Multi-center, randomized, evaluator-blinded. Primary endpoint: ≥1-point improvement on Mid-Face Volume Scale (MFVAS) at 6 months. Responder rate: ~82% at 6 months. Statistically significant vs control. Duration endpoint: sustained response to 24 months. [FDA label NDA 125474]\n\n**Chin augmentation study:** FDA approval 2021. Study population adults ≥22 years with chin region augmentation need. [FDA label update 2021]\n\n**Key publications:**\n- Baumann L et al. Aesthet Surg J 2015 — Real-world cheek volume, Vycross mechanism\n- Jones D et al. Aesthet Surg J 2016 — Pivotal trial data review\n- Sundaram H et al. J Drugs Dermatol 2015 — Vycross technology physicochemical characterization\n- Rohrich R et al. Plast Reconstr Surg 2019 — Facial fat compartment anatomy for injection planning\n\n## Comparison Anchors\n\n| Parameter | Voluma XC | Vollure XC | Ultra XC |\n|-----------|-----------|------------|----------|\n| G'' (lift capacity) | High (~800 Pa) | Medium | Medium-Low |\n| Indication | Cheeks, chin, midface lift | NLF, perioral lines | Lips, NLF, fine lines |\n| Duration | 18-24 months | 12-18 months | 9-12 months |\n| Technology | Vycross | Vycross | Vycross |\n| Optimal plane | Supraperiosteal / deep subdermal | Mid-dermal | Superficial to mid-dermal |\n\nGateway posture: duration and G'' values are reported ranges from published data; individual outcomes vary. For exact specifications, refer to prescribing information.',
  '8044bea2-d637-4251-89e4-0f420699eab0',
  'draft', 1
);

