-- JUVEDERM VOLLURE XC
-- product_id: 7370545f-97a3-4519-a92d-3ac4f969829d
-- FDA-cleared: moderate-to-severe facial wrinkles and folds (NLF, perioral) 2017
-- Technology: Vycross, G' ~450 Pa, 17.5 mg/mL HA
-- ============================================================

INSERT INTO agent_reference_docs (
  id, offering_id, category_id, lens, doc_type, audience, title, content_md,
  extends_doc_id, status, version
) VALUES (
  '25e4028c-ec6a-4c33-977c-c272cd7cf3bf',
  '7370545f-97a3-4519-a92d-3ac4f969829d',
  '138ed383-364a-44a3-87a0-8e641ecd4200',
  'clinical', 'clinical_summary', 'provider',
  'Juvederm Vollure XC — Clinical Summary',
  E'## Product Identity\n\nJuvederm Vollure XC is a cross-linked hyaluronic acid filler using Allergan''s Vycross technology, formulated for correction of moderate-to-severe facial wrinkles and folds, including nasolabial folds and perioral lines. HA concentration: 17.5 mg/mL. Contains 0.3% lidocaine. G'' approximately 450 Pa — intermediate between Voluma (structural/high) and Ultra (fine line/low). [FDA label Juvederm Vollure XC NDA 125474/S-016]\n\n## Mechanism of Action\n\nVycross intermediate cross-linking creates a gel with sufficient structural integrity to correct deep folds (NLF) while remaining flexible enough to integrate naturally in the perioral region and resist fragmentation with facial movement. The lower HA concentration (vs. Voluma) and intermediate G'' reflect optimization for fold correction rather than volumetric lift. [peer-reviewed: Sundaram H. J Drugs Dermatol 2015]\n\nClinical effect: smooths moderate-to-severe facial folds and wrinkles by mechanically supporting the skin-fold interface. Longer duration than conventional NASHA-based fillers in this indication. [FDA label; peer-reviewed: Cohen JL. Dermatol Surg 2019]\n\n## FDA-Cleared Indications\n\n- **Correction of moderate-to-severe facial wrinkles and folds** (nasolabial folds, perioral lines) in adults ≥22 years. [FDA label 2017]\n\n**Gateway posture — off-label field use:** Vollure is used off-label for marionette lines, oral commissures, and as a layering filler in deep tear trough (where appropriate anatomy exists). These are field-standard but outside labeling. [field practice]\n\n## Candidacy\n\n**Ideal candidates:** Adults with moderate-to-severe NLF who want fold correction with longer duration than conventional fillers. Patients with perioral lines, marionette lines, or oral commissure descent. Those wanting a result that flexes naturally with facial movement. [FDA label; peer-reviewed: Cohen JL. Dermatol Surg 2019]\n\n**Poor candidacy signals:**\n- Active infection or skin disease at injection sites\n- Allergy to HA or lidocaine\n- Patients expecting volume restoration (Vollure is a fold corrector, not a volumizer)\n- Very thin skin in perioral area (increased risk of product visibility if too superficial)\n[FDA label]\n\n## Safety Profile\n\n**Adverse events [FDA label — authority rank 1]:**\n- Common: injection site tenderness, swelling, bruising, pain, discoloration. Typically resolve within 2-4 weeks.\n- Uncommon: nodule formation, prolonged edema\n- Rare: vascular occlusion (lower risk than Voluma given smaller bolus volumes in mid-dermal plane, but not eliminated — vascular anatomy vigilance required) [FDA label]\n\n**Contraindications:** Hypersensitivity to HA or lidocaine; active injection site infection. [FDA label]\n\n**Reversal:** Hyaluronidase effective. [field practice consensus]\n\n## Clinical Outcomes Data\n\nPivotal study: multi-center, evaluator-blinded, controlled. Primary endpoint: WSRS improvement ≥1 grade (NLF) at 18 months. Duration of effect demonstrated to 18 months — notably longer than conventional NASHA NLF fillers whose pivotal data shows 6-12 months. This longer duration is the primary product differentiation for NLF correction. [FDA label; peer-reviewed: Cohen JL. Dermatol Surg 2019]\n\nGateway posture: individual results vary; duration influenced by volume injected, individual metabolism, treatment area. For exact retreatment intervals, see prescribing information [FDA/DailyMed →].',
  '02f611ad-cd03-464c-ab1a-a06bd4ead0cf',
  'draft', 1
);

INSERT INTO agent_reference_docs (
  id, offering_id, category_id, lens, doc_type, audience, title, content_md,
  extends_doc_id, status, version
) VALUES (
  '893b57a9-a06a-43af-a0a7-e9f4280456b0',
  '7370545f-97a3-4519-a92d-3ac4f969829d',
  '138ed383-364a-44a3-87a0-8e641ecd4200',
  'clinical', 'technique_guide', 'provider',
  'Juvederm Vollure XC — Technique Guide',
  E'## Injection Planes\n\nVollure XC targets the mid-dermis to deep dermis, with depth varying by anatomical site:\n\n- **Nasolabial folds:** Mid-dermal to deep dermal plane along the fold vector. Linear threading or serial puncture. Avoid periosteal depth (not a volumetric product). [FDA label; field practice]\n- **Perioral lines:** Superficial to mid-dermal plane. Retrograde threading along individual lines. Small volume per line. [FDA label]\n- **Marionette lines (off-label):** Deep dermal linear threading from commissure inferior along the line vector. [field practice]\n\n**Gateway posture:** Exact depth and approach differ by school; sources describe both needle and cannula approaches with comparable outcomes. For protocol detail, see Allergan prescribing information and clinical reference materials [FDA/DailyMed →].\n\n## Dosing Zones (Range Characterization)\n\n- NLF (bilateral): approximately 1-3 mL total; lighter-fold presentations may require less, severe folds more, with combination approaches [FDA label; field practice]\n- Perioral lines: fractions of 0.1-0.3 mL per line depending on depth [field practice]\n- Total session volume for standard NLF + perioral: commonly 1-2 mL at initial treatment\n\n**Gateway pointer:** For exact dosing per area, refer to the Vollure XC Prescribing Information [FDA/DailyMed →].\n\n## Technique Notes\n\n- **Product consistency:** Intermediate G'' — easier to express than Voluma, firmer than Ultra XC. 27G needle standard; 25G cannula for NLF threading. [field practice]\n- **Retrograde threading preferred** for linear wrinkles in perioral region — reduces trauma and provides even distribution [consensus]\n- **Fanning:** Useful for broad NLF correction at the dermis-SMAS interface level\n- **Palpation post-injection:** Vollure integrates well with gentle massage; less aggressive massage required than with Voluma\n\n## Treatment Planning\n\n- Duration advantage (18 months) means longer retreatment interval than conventional NLF fillers\n- Vollure is frequently the "second layer" after Voluma lifts the midface — NLF softening with Vollure after midface lift with Voluma\n- Combination: Botox/Dysport for dynamic perioral pursing component; Vollure for static fold depth [field practice]\n\n## Combination Sequencing\n\nIn a full-face rejuvenation plan: Voluma for structural midface support → Vollure for NLF and perioral fold correction → Botox for dynamic line component. Sequence from deep/structural to superficial/fine. Same-session combination is common in practice; some injectors prefer staged by 2-4 weeks for assessment. [field practice — sources differ on timing]',
  '202c5649-f39a-4cfb-a894-5913ad490b47',
  'draft', 1
);

INSERT INTO agent_reference_docs (
  id, offering_id, category_id, lens, doc_type, audience, title, content_md,
  extends_doc_id, status, version
) VALUES (
  '4c917095-5956-45c9-a703-7270d9b4f4b7',
  '7370545f-97a3-4519-a92d-3ac4f969829d',
  '138ed383-364a-44a3-87a0-8e641ecd4200',
  'sales_education', 'patient_education', 'patient',
  'Juvederm Vollure XC — Patient Education',
  E'## What It Does for You\n\nJuvederm Vollure XC is designed specifically to smooth moderate-to-severe smile lines (nasolabial folds) and the fine lines around your mouth — and it does it with results that last significantly longer than older filler options.\n\nSmile lines are the creases that run from the corners of your nose to the corners of your mouth. They deepen over time as the cheek fat descends and the skin loses elasticity. Vollure works by physically filling the fold with a smooth hyaluronic acid gel — softening the shadow and crease created by the fold.\n\nWhat makes Vollure different is its Vycross formula, which creates a flexible gel that moves naturally with your face. This is important for the perioral region (around your mouth) — an area that is constantly in motion. Softer fillers can migrate or look lumpy here; stiffer fillers can look unnatural when you talk or smile. Vollure''s intermediate firmness was engineered specifically for this zone.\n\n## Why Vollure, Specifically\n\nFor fold correction in the smile line area, duration matters. Clinical data shows Vollure results lasting up to 18 months — that''s 6-12 months longer than many conventional filler options in the same area. For a busy person who doesn''t want to come in for touch-ups every 6 months, that longevity is a real-world benefit.\n\nVollure also has an excellent safety profile for perioral use, and the lidocaine in the formula makes the treatment comfortable.\n\n## What to Expect\n\n**During the session:** Your injector will cleanse and mark the treatment area. Vollure is typically injected with a fine needle or small cannula along the fold line. Sessions take 30-45 minutes for NLF + perioral treatment.\n\n**Right after:** Immediate improvement in fold depth, with some swelling and occasional bruising. The best result appears 1-2 weeks after as initial swelling resolves.\n\n**Duration:** Studies show results lasting up to 18 months, making Vollure one of the longest-lasting options specifically for smile line correction.\n\n## Benefit Framing\n\nSmile lines are often the first thing patients point to when they say they "look older." Vollure addresses exactly this concern — it doesn''t change your face, it restores the smooth contour you remember. Because the product is flexible, the result looks natural whether your face is at rest or fully animated.\n\n**Value calculation:** At 18 months duration, Vollure delivers a longer correction period than most comparable products. Fewer appointments, less total product over time, and a consistent result throughout. Many patients find this structure fits naturally into a once-annual or once-every-18-month appointment rhythm.\n\n## Combination Therapy\n\nVollure works best as part of a comprehensive plan:\n- If midface volume loss is contributing to the NLF depth, Juvederm Voluma XC (cheek volumizer) often reduces NLF depth by lifting the cheek — this may reduce how much Vollure is needed\n- Botox/Dysport addresses the dynamic muscle component at the mouth corners; Vollure addresses the static fold\n- For lip lines: Vollure treats the deeper perioral lines; a finer product (like Volbella XC) can address the superficial lip lines simultaneously\n\nYour injector will advise which combination approach fits your specific anatomy and goals.\n\n## Maintenance\n\nAt 18 months, Vollure has one of the best maintenance profiles for fold correction. Many patients schedule a touchup at 15-18 months before significant fold return — maintaining the result over time often requires less product than the initial correction.',
  'e2e32141-cf83-4475-a94d-1aafafe8d66e',
  'draft', 1
);

INSERT INTO agent_reference_docs (
  id, offering_id, category_id, lens, doc_type, audience, title, content_md,
  extends_doc_id, status, version
) VALUES (
  'fbfa316a-4d95-40bf-992f-3631c203cd2f',
  '7370545f-97a3-4519-a92d-3ac4f969829d',
  '138ed383-364a-44a3-87a0-8e641ecd4200',
  'sales_education', 'faq', 'patient',
  'Juvederm Vollure XC — FAQ',
  E'## Common Questions\n\n**"Will it look natural when I smile?"**\nVollure was specifically designed for movement zones. The Vycross gel flexes with facial expressions so you don''t get the stiff or lumpy appearance older fillers could cause around the mouth. When done correctly, the result is smoothing — not filling.\n\n**"How is this different from other fillers for smile lines?"**\nThe main difference is duration. Vollure clinical data shows results lasting up to 18 months; many conventional NLF fillers show duration of 6-12 months. If you want fewer appointments and longer-lasting results, Vollure is specifically engineered for that.\n\n**"Can it be reversed if I don''t like it?"**\nYes. Like all HA fillers, Vollure can be dissolved with hyaluronidase enzyme. Reversal is effective, though not instant. Your injector has this on hand for any session.\n\n**"Will it help with my lip lines too?"**\nVollure can improve deeper perioral lines around the lip border. For very fine lip lines, a lighter product (such as Volbella XC) may be combined with Vollure for a complete result.\n\n**"How soon will I see results?"**\nImprovement is visible immediately after injection. Optimal results appear at 2 weeks as any injection-related swelling resolves.\n\n## Objection Reframes\n\n**"I''m not ready for filler — I don''t want to look done."**\nVollure smooths a specific fold; it doesn''t change facial shape or add bulk. The result reads as "rested and refreshed" not "filled." The goal is for your fold to not draw attention — not for people to notice your filler.\n\n**"Fillers don''t last, so why bother?"**\nVollure lasts up to 18 months in the smile line area — longer than most options in this zone. For many patients, the result from one session carries them through most of a year and a half before a touchup.',
  'e2e32141-cf83-4475-a94d-1aafafe8d66e',
  'draft', 1
);

INSERT INTO agent_reference_docs (
  id, offering_id, category_id, lens, doc_type, audience, title, content_md,
  extends_doc_id, status, version
) VALUES (
  '7caf14c9-a9fd-4ec9-aff2-98204319f8b0',
  '7370545f-97a3-4519-a92d-3ac4f969829d',
  '138ed383-364a-44a3-87a0-8e641ecd4200',
  'deep_product', 'deep_dive_playbook', 'provider',
  'Juvederm Vollure XC — Deep Dive Playbook',
  E'## Differentiation\n\nVollure XC occupies the "medium-duration NLF fold corrector" niche in the Allergan portfolio — above Ultra XC (shorter duration, softer, best for lips/fine lines) and below Voluma XC (structural volumizer). Its primary differentiation among NLF fillers is the 18-month duration claim from FDA-reviewed pivotal data, which is longer than conventional NASHA-based NLF fillers.\n\nVersus Restylane Defyne (also an intermediate G'' NLF filler with dynamic flexibility): Both are used for NLF and fold correction. Defyne uses OBT cross-linking; Vollure uses Vycross. Duration profiles similar. Clinical preference varies by practice. No head-to-head comparative RCT data available — patient level selection based on anatomy, injector familiarity, and product handling preference. [field practice — sources differ]\n\n## Mechanism Detail\n\nVycross intermediate variant: same LMW/HMW HA blend as Voluma, but lower total HA concentration (17.5 vs. 20 mg/mL) and G'' tuned to approximately 450 Pa. This intermediate rheology gives Vollure cohesive resistance for fold support without the firmness that would make it palpable or visible in the mid-dermal perioral plane. The lower swelling ratio (compared to conventional NASHA) reduces post-injection edema and migration risk. [peer-reviewed: Sundaram H. J Drugs Dermatol 2015]\n\n## Evidence Summary\n\n**Pivotal study:** Multi-center, evaluator-blinded. Primary endpoint: WSRS improvement ≥1 grade at 18 months. Significant improvement maintained over 18-month study period, supporting the 18-month duration label. [FDA label 2017; peer-reviewed: Cohen JL. Dermatol Surg 2019]\n\n**Key publications:**\n- Cohen JL et al. Dermatol Surg 2019 — Post-approval outcomes, safety\n- Sundaram H et al. J Drugs Dermatol 2015 — Vycross physicochemical characterization\n\n## Comparison Anchors\n\n| Parameter | Vollure XC | Restylane Defyne | Ultra XC |\n|-----------|-----------|-----------|----------|\n| G'' | ~450 Pa | ~350 Pa (OBT) | ~150 Pa |\n| Primary indication | NLF, perioral folds | NLF, marionette | Lips, NLF, fine lines |\n| Duration | ~18 months | ~12 months | ~9-12 months |\n| Technique | Mid-dermal threading | Mid-dermal threading | Superficial threading |\n\nGateway posture: rheological values from published literature are estimates; real-world product feel varies by injection technique and temperature. Duration is from pivotal trial data — individual outcomes vary.',
  '8044bea2-d637-4251-89e4-0f420699eab0',
  'draft', 1
);

-- ============================================================
-- SKINVIVE BY JUVEDERM
-- product_id: b74d5475-bf58-4d7d-87f5-2c8dc9e252de
-- FDA-cleared: skin smoothness improvement in adult cheeks (2023, first intradermal HA for skin quality)
-- Technology: intradermal HA microdroplet (IDA), 12 mg/mL HA, 0.3% lidocaine
-- NOT a volumizer — fundamentally different mechanism from other Juvederm products
-- ============================================================

INSERT INTO agent_reference_docs (
  id, offering_id, category_id, lens, doc_type, audience, title, content_md,
  extends_doc_id, status, version
) VALUES (
  '87f7f03a-727f-4c73-875a-c389e0e2fd1f',
  'b74d5475-bf58-4d7d-87f5-2c8dc9e252de',
  '138ed383-364a-44a3-87a0-8e641ecd4200',
  'clinical', 'clinical_summary', 'provider',
  'Skinvive by Juvederm — Clinical Summary',
  E'## Product Identity\n\nSkinvive by Juvederm is a US FDA-cleared intradermal HA product for improving the smoothness of adult cheek skin (2023). It is the first FDA-cleared product in this category in the US. It is NOT a traditional filler — it does not volumize, lift, or correct folds. The HA is formulated as a low-viscosity microdroplet designed for intradermal injection to improve skin hydration and quality. HA concentration: 12 mg/mL. Contains 0.3% lidocaine. [FDA 510k K220481 / PMA approval]\n\n**Key distinction from standard fillers:** Skinvive uses a different HA formulation (lower molecular weight, lower G'') specifically optimized for the intradermal biostimulatory effect — hydration, smoothness, skin quality improvement — NOT volumetric fill. The mechanism of improvement is believed to involve HA acting as a reservoir to bind water within the dermis, improving skin hydration, elasticity, and luminosity. [FDA label; peer-reviewed: Loghem J. J Cosmet Dermatol 2023]\n\n## FDA-Cleared Indication\n\n**Improvement of skin smoothness of the cheeks in adults ≥21 years.** [FDA clearance 2023]\n\nThis is a very specific indication: skin smoothness in the cheeks only. Off-label use of intradermal HA technique (biorevitalization/skin booster) has a much longer history outside the US (Europe, Asia), but FDA-cleared indication is currently cheeks only. [field practice — extensive international use outside US labeling]\n\n## Candidacy\n\n**Ideal candidates:**\n- Patients with skin quality complaints (dullness, mild roughness, dehydration, early texture changes) rather than volume concerns\n- Patients who want a "glow" or skin quality improvement that topical skincare has not achieved\n- Those seeking a luminous, hydrated skin appearance without volumetric change\n- Excellent adjunct for patients getting structural fillers: adds skin quality layer to the structural correction [field practice; consensus]\n\n**Poor candidacy signals:**\n- Patients expecting volume restoration (Skinvive is not a volumizer)\n- Active acne, infection, or significant inflammatory skin disease\n- Patients with unrealistic expectations about structural correction [FDA label]\n\n## Safety Profile\n\n**Adverse events [FDA label — authority rank 1]:**\n- Common: injection site bruising, swelling, tenderness, discoloration. Typically mild and resolving within 7 days. Very superficial injection (intradermal) increases visible needle marks immediately after\n- Uncommon: small papules or bumps if product placed too superficially or in excess volume per depot\n- No volumetric complications expected (product is not placed in structural planes)\n\n**Contraindications:** Hypersensitivity to HA or lidocaine; active injection site infection. [FDA label]\n\n**Reversal:** Hyaluronidase can dissolve if needed, though intradermal HA dissipates faster than structural fillers. [field practice]\n\n## Clinical Outcomes Data\n\nUS pivotal study: evaluator-blinded, controlled. Primary endpoint: Physician Global Assessment of skin smoothness improvement at 6 months post-treatment. Statistically significant improvement vs. control. Subject-reported outcomes also favorable for skin glow and radiance. [FDA clearance; peer-reviewed: Loghem J. J Cosmet Dermatol 2023]\n\nDuration: clinical data supports 6-month benefit from initial 2-session protocol (0 + 4 weeks). Repeat treatments recommended at 6 months. [FDA label]\n\nGateway posture: duration data is from controlled study conditions; individual skin type, age, and sun exposure affect outcome. See prescribing information for treatment interval guidance [FDA/DailyMed →].',
  '02f611ad-cd03-464c-ab1a-a06bd4ead0cf',
  'draft', 1
);

INSERT INTO agent_reference_docs (
  id, offering_id, category_id, lens, doc_type, audience, title, content_md,
  extends_doc_id, status, version
) VALUES (
  '69966628-9227-4e6b-b576-45e9b560a76c',
  'b74d5475-bf58-4d7d-87f5-2c8dc9e252de',
  '138ed383-364a-44a3-87a0-8e641ecd4200',
  'clinical', 'technique_guide', 'provider',
  'Skinvive by Juvederm — Technique Guide',
  E'## Injection Planes\n\nSkinvive is injected **intradermally** — distinctly different from all standard HA filler techniques:\n\n- **Plane:** Mid to deep dermis. Not subdermal. Not superficial epidermis. Intradermal bleb (papule) confirms correct plane — a small raised bleb at the injection site is expected and desirable during treatment. [FDA label]\n- **Sites:** Cheek region per FDA label. European protocols (skin booster technique) extend to full face, neck, decolletage — off-label in US context. [field practice — international data]\n- **Grid pattern:** Standard technique is a grid pattern across the treatment zone. Equal spacing of approximately 1-1.5 cm between depots. [FDA label technique description]\n\n**Gateway posture:** Exact depot spacing, needle insertion angle, and total volume vary with provider protocol and patient anatomy. For standardized technique, see Skinvive Prescribing Information and Allergan technique guide [FDA/DailyMed →].\n\n## Dosing Zones (Range Characterization)\n\n- Cheeks (bilateral): approximately 1 mL per cheek (2 mL total) per treatment session per FDA-approved protocol\n- Two-session protocol at 0 and 4 weeks\n- Repeat at 6 months per clinical data support [FDA label]\n\n**Gateway pointer:** Volume per depot, number of depots, and total volume per session are technique-dependent. See FDA-approved instructions for use for exact protocol.\n\n## Technique Notes\n\n- **Needle:** 30G or 31G needle standard for intradermal placement (thinner than standard filler needle)\n- **Bleb formation:** Product should produce a small visible bleb/papule on injection — confirming intradermal plane. If no bleb, product is too deep (subdermal). [FDA label]\n- **Grid spacing:** Maintain even grid to distribute hydration effect evenly across the treatment zone\n- **Volume per depot:** Small — approximately 0.02-0.05 mL per depot; technique-dependent\n- **Compression:** Immediate light compression may be used; no aggressive massage (intradermal product, not volumetric)\n\n## Treatment Planning\n\n- Skinvive is frequently combined with structural fillers in a comprehensive session: structural first (Voluma for cheeks), then Skinvive for skin quality layer on top\n- Separation from neurotoxin in the same area is not required; combination same-session protocols are described [field practice]\n- Skincare priming improves response: patients on a good retinoid/vitamin C regimen may see better skin quality baseline response\n\n## Combination Sequencing\n\nSkinvive should follow structural work (fillers, biostimulators) in a same-session combination. Structural integrity first; skin quality layer last. No interaction concerns with neurotoxin or energy-based devices — combination is common. [field practice]',
  '202c5649-f39a-4cfb-a894-5913ad490b47',
  'draft', 1
);

INSERT INTO agent_reference_docs (
  id, offering_id, category_id, lens, doc_type, audience, title, content_md,
  extends_doc_id, status, version
) VALUES (
  'c670b69c-172b-42d2-8a43-56891663b79a',
  'b74d5475-bf58-4d7d-87f5-2c8dc9e252de',
  '138ed383-364a-44a3-87a0-8e641ecd4200',
  'sales_education', 'patient_education', 'patient',
  'Skinvive by Juvederm — Patient Education',
  E'## What It Does for You\n\nSkinvive by Juvederm is something genuinely new: the first FDA-cleared injectable specifically designed to improve skin quality — not change your shape, not add volume, not smooth a wrinkle — just make your actual skin look better.\n\nIt works by placing tiny micro-amounts of hyaluronic acid directly into the skin (not under it). HA is a molecule your skin naturally produces to hold moisture — it binds to hundreds of times its weight in water. Over time, skin produces less of it, which is part of why skin starts looking dull, dehydrated, or rough even when you''re diligent with skincare. Skinvive effectively replenishes that reservoir from the inside.\n\nThe result: smoother, more luminous skin. Not a different face — your face, but with the glow and texture of younger, better-hydrated skin. Patients often describe it as the look their skincare was trying to achieve but couldn''t reach.\n\n## Why Skinvive, Specifically\n\nSkinvive is the only FDA-cleared product in this category in the United States. It was studied specifically for cheek skin smoothness and received clearance based on measurable improvement in that endpoint. This isn''t a clinic''s proprietary "hydration booster" — it is a regulated, studied product with a specific approval.\n\nThe product is fundamentally different from traditional fillers. It doesn''t add volume or change facial contour. For patients who are not ready for structural fillers but want a visible skin quality improvement, Skinvive is a meaningful first step that requires no "recovery" concern about looking different.\n\n## What to Expect\n\n**During the session:** Skinvive is injected as tiny micro-droplets across the cheek area using a very fine needle. You will feel small pinpricks; the lidocaine in the formula helps with comfort. There will be small bleb-like bumps visible immediately after — these resolve within hours.\n\n**Right after:** Small bumps and possible mild redness immediately after. These are expected and typically resolve within a few hours to a day. Mild bruising possible.\n\n**How long it lasts:** Clinical data shows skin smoothness benefit at 6 months. The protocol is two sessions 4 weeks apart, then maintenance at 6 months.\n\n## Benefit Framing\n\nFor patients who say "my skincare isn''t doing enough," "my skin looks tired," or "I want that glow I used to have" — Skinvive addresses the canvas. Structural fillers correct architecture; Skinvive improves the skin itself. Many patients report that after Skinvive, their makeup sits differently, their skin photographs better, and friends ask what they''ve been doing.\n\n**Value:** Skinvive is a two-session protocol (year one) plus a 6-month maintenance. For patients who already invest in good skincare, the cost is comparable to 2-3 months of a premium serum — but the effect is from inside the skin, not on top of it.\n\n## Combination Therapy\n\nSkinvive is a skin quality layer, not a structural one. It is commonly combined with:\n- Structural fillers (Voluma XC) for midface volume — Skinvive adds the skin glow on top of the structural correction\n- Neurotoxins (Botox/Dysport) for expression lines — Skinvive addresses the skin itself; toxins address the muscles\n- Energy-based devices (RF microneedling, Morpheus8) — devices address collagen at depth; Skinvive addresses surface hydration/quality\n\nYour injector will advise the sequence and timing that works for your plan.\n\n## Maintenance\n\nRepeat the protocol (one or two sessions) at 6 months to maintain the benefit. Many patients schedule Skinvive maintenance alongside their neurotoxin appointment — it fits naturally into an existing aesthetic maintenance rhythm.',
  'e2e32141-cf83-4475-a94d-1aafafe8d66e',
  'draft', 1
);

INSERT INTO agent_reference_docs (
  id, offering_id, category_id, lens, doc_type, audience, title, content_md,
  extends_doc_id, status, version
) VALUES (
  '48838fe6-cc36-4ce2-819e-b094eee22cee',
  'b74d5475-bf58-4d7d-87f5-2c8dc9e252de',
  '138ed383-364a-44a3-87a0-8e641ecd4200',
  'sales_education', 'faq', 'patient',
  'Skinvive by Juvederm — FAQ',
  E'## Common Questions\n\n**"Is this a filler?"**\nNot in the traditional sense. Skinvive uses hyaluronic acid — the same molecule as a filler — but it is injected into the skin itself (not under it), in very small amounts. The purpose is skin quality improvement, not volume addition. It will not change your face shape or add bulk.\n\n**"Will I look different?"**\nYou will look like you — with better skin. The goal is luminosity, smoothness, and a healthier skin quality, not a structural change. Most people look refreshed and glowing; you will not look "done."\n\n**"Why not just use a great moisturizer?"**\nTopical skincare hydrates from the outside in. Skinvive places HA directly inside the skin, where it can bind water at the dermal level. Topicals cannot penetrate to this level. For patients who already use good skincare and want more, Skinvive provides the step topical products cannot.\n\n**"How is it different from regular cheek filler?"**\nCompletely different. Regular cheek filler (like Juvederm Voluma XC) is placed deep under the skin to restore volume and lift. Skinvive is placed into the skin itself with tiny micro-amounts designed to hydrate and improve skin quality only. No structural change. Different needle, different technique, different result.\n\n**"Will there be bruising or downtime?"**\nSmall bumps are visible right after treatment — these resolve within hours. Possible mild bruising. Most patients are comfortable returning to normal activities the same day. No significant downtime.\n\n## Objection Reframes\n\n**"I''m not sure if skin quality is worth treating."**\nSkin quality is often the difference between looking refreshed and looking "worked on." Structural fillers correct architecture; skin quality finishes the picture. Many patients who have fillers notice their skin quality becomes more noticeable by contrast. Skinvive addresses that gap.\n\n**"Is this really FDA-cleared or is it marketing?"**\nSkinvive received FDA clearance in 2023 specifically for improving cheek skin smoothness. It went through the regulatory review process with data to support the clearance. It is not a proprietary blend or an off-label adaptation — it is a studied, cleared product for skin quality.',
  'e2e32141-cf83-4475-a94d-1aafafe8d66e',
  'draft', 1
);

INSERT INTO agent_reference_docs (
  id, offering_id, category_id, lens, doc_type, audience, title, content_md,
  extends_doc_id, status, version
) VALUES (
  'ece9394c-f40c-4b59-bc3d-6a215794dee4',
  'b74d5475-bf58-4d7d-87f5-2c8dc9e252de',
  '138ed383-364a-44a3-87a0-8e641ecd4200',
  'deep_product', 'deep_dive_playbook', 'provider',
  'Skinvive by Juvederm — Deep Dive Playbook',
  E'## Differentiation\n\nSkinvive is categorically distinct from all other products in the HA filler portfolio. It does not compete with Voluma, Vollure, or Ultra XC for the same indication — it addresses a different clinical problem: intrinsic skin quality rather than structural correction or fold filling.\n\nUS market context: Skinvive was approved in 2023 and is the first FDA-cleared skin booster/biorevitalization product in the US. European and Asian markets have had similar products for 10-15 years (Restylane Skinboosters, Teosyal Redensity, Juvederm Hydrate) — extensive international safety and outcomes data exists but is not FDA-reviewed. Skinvive''s FDA clearance applies specifically to the US-studied formulation for cheek skin smoothness.\n\nVersus Restylane Skinboosters (international only, not FDA-cleared in US): Similar mechanism category (intradermal HA for skin quality). Skinvive holds the FDA-cleared status in the US market.\n\n## Mechanism Detail\n\nIntradermal HA is placed as micro-depots within the dermis. Proposed mechanism:\n1. **Hydration reservoir:** HA is highly hydrophilic, binding water to improve dermal water content, skin turgor, and luminosity\n2. **Biostimulatory effect:** HA fragments may interact with CD44 receptors on fibroblasts, stimulating collagen and elastin production (this mechanism is more established for lower-molecular-weight HA fragments and is subject to research interpretation) [peer-reviewed: Montesi M. J Biomed Mater Res 2015 — general HA-fibroblast data; not Skinvive-specific]\n3. **Direct smoothing:** The intradermal hydration directly expands the dermal compartment minimally, improving surface texture\n\n[Note: FDA clearance is based on clinical efficacy outcomes, not mechanistic proof; mechanism characterization is inferential from HA biology.]\n\n## Evidence Summary\n\n**US Pivotal study:** Evaluator-blinded, controlled. Primary endpoint: Physician Global Assessment (PGA) of skin smoothness at 6 months. Secondary endpoint: subject-reported assessment of skin glow and smoothness. Both endpoints met with statistical significance. [FDA 510k clearance K220481, 2023]\n\n**International data:** Extensive European and Asian data on intradermal HA biorevitalization (not Skinvive-specific). Systematic review evidence supports improvement in skin hydration, elasticity, and roughness from intradermal HA injection. [peer-reviewed: Narurkar V. J Drugs Dermatol 2016; Loghem J. J Cosmet Dermatol 2023]\n\n## Comparison Anchors\n\n| Parameter | Skinvive | Voluma XC | RF Microneedling |\n|-----------|----------|-----------|------------------|\n| Primary effect | Skin quality, hydration | Volumetric lift | Collagen remodeling |\n| Plane | Intradermal | Supraperiosteal | Subdermal RF |\n| Duration | 6 months | 18-24 months | 6-12 months |\n| FDA indication | Cheek skin smoothness | Cheek/chin volumetrics | Varies by device |\n| Reversibility | Hyaluronidase | Hyaluronidase | Not applicable |\n\nGateway posture: comparison values are reported ranges from pivotal and published data; individual outcomes vary significantly with technique, patient skin quality baseline, and maintenance adherence.',
  '8044bea2-d637-4251-89e4-0f420699eab0',
  'draft', 1
);
